Package bio.singa.mathematics.concepts

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Addable<NumberConcept extends Addable<NumberConcept>>
    The "addition" operation can be any commutative and associative binary operation on a number concept.
    AdditivelyInvertible<NumberConcept>
    The "additive inversion" operation can be any unary operation that returns the "opposite" of this Object.
    Divisible<NumberConcept extends Divisible<NumberConcept>>
    The "division" operation can be any anticommutative and not associative binary operation on a number concept.
    Invertible<NumberConcept>
    In abstract algebra, the idea of an inverse element generalizes concepts of a negation.
    MultiDimensional<NumberConcept extends MultiDimensional<NumberConcept>>
    The MultiDimensional interface defines whether a Number concept has one or more Dimensions.
    Multipliable<NumberConcept extends Multipliable<NumberConcept>>
    The "multiplication" operation can be any commutative and associative binary operation on a number concept.
    MultiplicativelyInvertible<NumberConcept>
    The multiplicative inverse of a number and the number itself combined with an multiplicative operation yield the neutral element (One Element).
    Ring<RingType extends Addable<RingType> & Subtractable<RingType> & Multipliable<RingType>>  
    Subtractable<NumberConcept extends Subtractable<NumberConcept>>
    The "subtraction" operation can be any anticommutative and not associative binary operation on a number concept.
